Package com.naef.jnlua

Provides the JNLua core types, such as the Lua state class and the core interfaces.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Converter Converts between Lua values and Java objects.
JavaFunction Provides a Lua function implemented in Java.
JavaReflector Reflects Java objects for access from Lua.
LuaValueProxy Provides proxy access to a Lua value from Java.
NamedJavaFunction Provides a named Java function.
NativeSupport.Loader Loads the library.
TypedJavaObject Represents a Java object with an explicit type.
 

Class Summary
Activator  
DefaultConverter Default implementation of the Converter interface.
DefaultJavaReflector Default implementation of the JavaReflector interface.
JavaModule Provides the Java module for Lua.
LuaStackTraceElement Represents an execution point in a Lua stack trace.
LuaState JNLua core class representing a Lua instance.
NativeSupport Loads the JNLua native library.
 

Enum Summary
JavaReflector.Metamethod Lua metamethod.
LuaState.GcAction Represents a Lua garbage collector action.
LuaState.Library Represents a Lua library.
LuaType Represents a Lua type.
 

Exception Summary
LuaException Abstract base class for Lua error conditions.
LuaMemoryAllocationException Indicates a Lua memory allocation error.
LuaRuntimeException Indicates a Lua runtime error.
LuaSyntaxException Indicates a Lua syntax error.
